The following is a list of notable software for running a [[BitTorrent tracker]].
{| class="wikitable sortable" border="1" |- ! Tracker ! Programming Language ! License ! Operating System Support ! Description |- | Atrack<ref>http://repo.cat-v.org/atrack/</ref> | [[Python (programming language)|Python]] | {{Free|[[Public Domain]]/[[MIT License|MIT]]}} | [[Google App Engine]], (or any host with [[Python (programming language)|Python]] and [[memcached]]) | Minimalist tracker designed to run efficiently on App Engine relying on memcached for all storage. |- | BNBT<ref>http://sourceforge.net/projects/bnbt</ref> | [[C++]] | {{Free|[[LGPL]]}} | Windows, (Linux or Mac?) | [[BNBT]] is a complete port of the original [[Python (programming language)|Python]] [[BitTorrent tracker]] to [[C++]] using the [[Standard Template Library|STL]] for data storage and basic network sockets for network communication. |- | Bitstorm<ref>https://stormhub.org/tracker/</ref> | [[PHP]] | {{Free|[[GPL]]}} | FreeBSD, Linux, Mac, Solaris, Windows | A compact and fast BitTorrent tracker implementation that works on any PHP compatible web server. Bitstorm tries to be a very simplistic tracker and only implements the very basic functions a tracker needs, making it easy to install and configure. |- | CBTT<ref>http://svn.depthstrike.com:4559/trac/masstorrent</ref> | [[C++]] | {{Free|[[LGPL]]}} | Windows, (Linux or Mac?) | CBTT is a modified version of BNBT. Uses Flat-file or MySQL databases. Capable of multiple-tracker clusters. |- | LeonidasP2P<ref>http://sourceforge.net/projects/leonidas/</ref> | [[ASP .Net|ASP .NET 2.0]] | {{Free|[[Shared source#Microsoft Reciprocal License (Ms-RL)|Microsoft Reciprocal License]]}} | Windows (Linux and Mac?) | Based on [[phpMyBitTorrent]] |- | LimeTracker<ref>http://limecast.com/tracker</ref> | [[PHP]] | {{Free|[[LGPL]]}} | Linux, Mac, Windows | Optionally uses [[MySQL]] for data storage, uses [[Symfony]] framework, sponsored by [[LimeWire]] |- | mod bt<ref>http://www.crackerjack.net/mod_bt/index.html</ref> | [[C Programming|C]] | {{Free|[[Apache License]]}} | Linux (Mac and Windows?) | [[Apache HTTP Server|Apache]] 2.X module, setup through Apache configuration file |- | [[MonoTorrent]]<ref>http://www.monotorrent.com</ref> | [[C Sharp (programming language)|C#]] | {{Free|[[MIT License|MIT]]}} | Linux, Mac, Windows | Uses [[Mono Project|Mono]] for cross-platform support (.NET) |- | [[Opentracker]]<ref>http://erdgeist.org/arts/software/opentracker/</ref> | [[C Programming|C]] | {{Free|[[Beerware]]}} | FreeBSD, Linux, Mac, Solaris, Windows,â¦ | Uses libowfat,<ref>http://www.fefe.de/libowfat/</ref> performs well even on [[embedded hardware]]. Only requirement is a [[POSIX]] compliant [[Operating system|OS]]. |- | OpenTracker<ref>http://www.whitsoftdev.com/opentracker/</ref> | [[PHP]] | {{?}} Not Specified | Linux, Mac, Windows | Uses [[MySQL]] for data storage, lightweight and simple |- | [[PeerTracker]]<ref>http://code.google.com/p/peertracker/</ref> | [[PHP]] | {{Free|[[GPL]]}} | [[Cross-platform]] | Extremely lightweight and efficient [[BitTorrent (protocol)|BitTorrent]] tracker. Supports [[SQLite3]], [[MySQL]] and soon [[PostgreSQL]] for storage. |- | PHPBTTracker+<ref>http://phpbttrkplus.sourceforge.net/</ref> | [[PHP]] | {{Free|[[GPL]]}} | Linux, others untested/unsupported | Uses [[MySQL]] for data storage |- | phpMyBitTorrent<ref>http://www.phpmybittorrent.com</ref> | [[PHP]] | {{Free|[[GPL]]}} | Linux, Mac, Windows | Uses [[MySQL]] for data storage |- | Project Gazelle<ref>http://what.cd/gazelle/</ref> | [[PHP]] | {{Free}} | Linux | Runs [[What.CD]],<ref>http://what.cd/</ref> a popular music tracker. It can be configured to work with various backends, including [[XBT Tracker|XBTT]] and the project's very own Ocelot.<ref>http://what.cd/wiki.php?action=article&name=Gazelle+Source+Code+-+Where+can+I+get+a+copy%3F</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://what.cd/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=109616|title=Ocelot: The story of a tracker|author=NightOath|publisher=What.cd}}</ref> |- | RivetTracker<ref>http://www.rivetcode.com/software/rivettracker/</ref> | [[PHP]] | {{Free|[[GPL]]}} | Linux, Mac, Windows | Uses [[MySQL]] for data storage, support for RSS feeds, HTTP seeding, detailed statistics, uses web-interface |- |TorrentTrader<ref>http://www.torrenttrader.org</ref><ref>http://sourceforge.net/projects/torrenttrader</ref> | [[PHP]] | {{Free|[[GPL]]}} | [[Cross-platform]] | Uses [[MySQL]] for data storage, support for RSS feeds, detailed statistics, web-interface. (Also has a light open tracker<ref>http://www.torrenttrader.org/index.php?s=&showtopic=11827&view=findpost&p=62027</ref> with no interface.) |- | [[Utorrent#Features|ÂµTorrent]]<ref>http://www.utorrent.com/faq/features#faq15</ref> | [[C++]] | {{Proprietary}} [[Freeware]] | Mac (Intel only), Windows / [[Wine (software)|Wine]] | Does not have a web interface or list of hosted torrents; it is not designed for secure or large-scale application |- | [[Vuze]]<ref>http://azureus.sourceforge.net/faq.php#17</ref> | [[Java (programming language)|Java]] | {{Free|[[GPL]]}} | Linux, Mac, Windows | [[Vuze]] (formerly Azureus) has a built in tracker. |- | XBNBT<ref>http://xbnbt.sourceforge.net/</ref> | [[C++]] | {{Free|[[LGPL]]}} | Linux, Mac, Windows | Modified version of [[BNBT]], uses flat-file or [[MySQL]] for data storage |- | [[XBT Tracker]]<ref>http://xbtt.sourceforge.net/tracker/</ref><ref>http://sourceforge.net/projects/xbtt/</ref> | [[C++]] | {{Free|[[GPL]]}} | Linux and Windows | Uses [[MySQL]] for data storage, lightweight tracker |}
